<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Harmony is used for pulling from static spawn points.  Assuming you are low level...go to a camp site such as the dervs, orcs, goblins, any site that has multiple guys just standing around.  Now, standing away from the camp, cast harmony.<P>I personally cast it on every mob to make sure I got them all, but it is AE and this is only a safety precaution.<P>Now that the whole camp is harmonied, you can safely pull singles (whether with a bow, spell or running up there quickly) from the camp.  However, you have to be sure you pull the mob away cause otherwise when harmony runs out you will be in trouble.<P>Harmony can also be used in places like City of Mist if you just want to run past guys without fighting them.<P>Note however that the mob has to stay put.  Harmony will not work on wandering mobs!<P>I think that about covers it.   <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0">
</FONT>
<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
