<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Thats odd, Harmony would not work for me in CoM... I was even told by others it doesnt work in that zone. I cast it on a few NPCs and they still agroed on me.<P>Something else to add, once a mob has the harmony effect on them, they can still be agroed by touch. If you or the mob you are pulling touch another NPC, harmony will break. It will even work on wondering NPCs. Before a recent patch if you were too far away you saw no spell effect at all. Now from any distance you can see the effect land on the target but not the NPCs around them. If you get near then you will see all the NPCs it affects.<P>So in an outdoor zone a druid can single pull any NPC they want with some skill and timing. It really is a great spell, take some time to master it. I think it makes druids better puller then monks because they can get NPCs deeper into a spawn then the first ones they enounter. An exsample... I am able to single pull the Ry'Gorr chief, or Blacksmith(I really want that hammer) from a full spawn, with little or no trouble.
</FONT>
